00:58.520 --> 01:01.398
<i>Ladies and gentlemen,
this is Charlie Chaplin talking.</i>

01:01.680 --> 01:04.194
<i>This is Hollywood,
California in 1915</i>

01:04.400 --> 01:06.516
<i>with its sun-kissed oranges
and lemon groves,</i>

01:06.720 --> 01:09.678
<i>before it was visited
by the 3 horsemen of the apocalypse:</i>

01:09.880 --> 01:11.791
<i>Oil, movies and aeronautics,</i>

01:12.040 --> 01:14.474
<i>who strolled the earth uprooting
the orange and lemon trees,</i>

01:14.680 --> 01:17.399
<i>and in their stead built factories
and motion picture studios.</i>

01:18.440 --> 01:19.634
<i>I was one of the offenders.</i>

01:19.840 --> 01:21.319
<i>I wanted a studio in a hurry.</i>

01:21.520 --> 01:23.238
<i>In the States,
they do things in a hurry.</i>

01:23.440 --> 01:24.668
<i>And, as if by magic,
I got it.</i>

01:25.720 --> 01:27.950
<i>This is not Stratford-on-Avon,
Shakespeare's birthplace.</i>

01:28.600 --> 01:30.875
<i>Believe it or not,
this is a motion picture studio.</i>

01:31.600 --> 01:33.556
<i>Now you see my arrival, that's me.</i>

01:34.360 --> 01:35.952
<i>I look much younger there.</i>

01:36.160 --> 01:38.310
<i>That was taken
at least 10 years ago.</i>

01:39.360 --> 01:40.873
<i>Now let me take you backstage.</i>

01:41.080 --> 01:43.310
<i>In those days I never worked
with a scenario.</i>

01:43.520 --> 01:45.829
<i>It started with an idea
and developed on the set.</i>

01:54.560 --> 01:57.597
<i>This is Miss Edna Purviance,
my leading lady.</i>

01:58.160 --> 02:00.958
<i>She's put on a little weight during
the building of the studio.</i>

02:06.080 --> 02:07.479
<i>In the next scene,
we ran into trouble.</i>

02:07.680 --> 02:09.636
<i>We must have rehearsed it 50 times.</i>

02:25.240 --> 02:28.357
<i>On the 32nd take the little fellow
became quite a dead weight.</i>

02:28.840 --> 02:31.149
<i>It was very trying on the muscles
of my arms.</i>

02:33.880 --> 02:36.952
<i>So now let me take you back
to the good old silent days.</i>

02:37.160 --> 02:39.754
<i>There will be no talk,
no realistic sound.</i>

02:39.960 --> 02:41.313
<i>I think it would spoil the mood.</i>

02:41.520 --> 02:43.875
<i>I have composed 2 hours of music
which I hope</i>

02:44.080 --> 02:48.358
<i>will be more agreeable than the sound
of footsteps on the gravel path.</i>

02:48.560 --> 02:51.199
<i>Or a lot of yackety-yak talking
as I'm doing now.</i>

02:51.680 --> 02:54.672
<i>There'll be music and action,
a sort of a comic ballet.</i>

02:55.040 --> 02:58.350
<i>And now I shall retire behind
my curtain of silence.</i>

