15:01.760 --> 15:04.320
<i>THE GREEN LANTERN</i>

15:06.200 --> 15:08.634
<i>NO DOGS ALLOWED</i>

16:56.840 --> 16:58.990
A new singer sings
an old song.

18:58.760 --> 19:01.479
"If you smile and
wink, they'll buy
a drink."

19:34.640 --> 19:36.039
"I'm flirting."

21:26.840 --> 21:28.637
"How about the lady?"

23:49.480 --> 23:51.755
"There are strangers
in our midst."

25:13.480 --> 25:15.516
Back to the Green Lantern.

27:16.200 --> 27:18.475
"We will settle down
in the country."

33:31.440 --> 33:33.192
When dreams
come true.

35:32.400 --> 35:34.630
<i>The next picture is a comedy
of the First World War.</i>

35:35.280 --> 35:37.589
<i>These are actual scenes
of the fighting,</i>

35:37.800 --> 35:39.756
<i>taken from the archives
of the Imperial War Museum.</i>

35:40.720 --> 35:42.472
<i>Fighting was different in those days.</i>

35:42.680 --> 35:43.749
<i>They lived in trenches for months,</i>

35:43.960 --> 35:45.473
<i>languishing in dugouts and mud</i>

35:45.680 --> 35:47.238
<i>until the fatal Zero Hour</i>

35:47.520 --> 35:50.557
<i>when they went over the top
and captured the enemy's trench.</i>

35:51.280 --> 35:52.269
<i>Half of them made it,</i>

35:52.480 --> 35:53.356
<i>half of them didn't.</i>

35:53.920 --> 35:55.956
<i>There were no atomic bombs
or guided missiles.</i>

35:56.160 --> 35:58.549
<i>Then, it was only cannons,
bayonets and poison gas.</i>

36:00.120 --> 36:02.190
<i>Those were the good old days.</i>

36:02.400 --> 36:04.072
<i>So now, Shoulder Arms.</i>

36:07.240 --> 36:10.835
SHOULDER ARMS

36:25.040 --> 36:26.792
The awkward squad.

37:46.800 --> 37:48.552
"Put those feet in."

38:45.120 --> 38:46.917
Over there.

40:49.640 --> 40:51.232
The enemy.

41:25.400 --> 41:27.072
A quiet lunch.

41:41.040 --> 41:42.837
"Make yourself
at home."

42:10.640 --> 42:11.755
Later.

42:30.360 --> 42:31.395
Changing quard.

42:33.480 --> 42:35.789
"The password --
<i>'It's wet'.</i>"

43:05.360 --> 43:06.713
News from home.

45:05.160 --> 45:07.515
"This must be yours."

45:47.360 --> 45:48.793
"To the day!"

46:10.960 --> 46:11.915
Bed time.

47:09.120 --> 47:10.678
"Stop rocking
the boat!"

48:02.840 --> 48:03.909
Morning.

48:52.760 --> 48:54.990
"Over the top in
fifteen minutes!"

50:34.480 --> 50:36.277
The captured trench.

50:41.520 --> 50:43.750
13 not so unlucky.

51:36.720 --> 51:38.711
"How did you capture
thirteen?"

51:40.840 --> 51:42.637
"I surrounded them."

52:05.880 --> 52:07.836
Two of a kind.

